  "texts": [
    "We chose Yule's Q to represent the extent of transitional associations because it has descriptive value and can account for base numbers of contributions (ranging from -1 to + 1, with zero indicating no association).",
    "This study used a network visualization technique previously developed (Chen et al., 2017) to illustrate the outcomes of LsA in networks.",
    "Nodes represent behavior codes along with their corresponding frequencies, while edges denote transitional Yule's Q values.",
    "An arrow pointing in the opposite direction of the node denotes the direction of the transition.",
    "Secondly, we evaluated the students' programming performance by assessing their programming assignments."
  ],
